gpt2-lora-int8
==============

This repository contains ORIGINAL work by Adrian Nagorka, Joel Håkansson, and
Nicholas Lawrance: from-scratch PyTorch implementations of LoRA fine-tuning and
post-training int8 weight-only quantisation, plus a self-contained demo, tests,
and the experimental results from our DD2424 course project.

Attribution and scope
----------------------
The experiments that produced the results reported here were run on top of the
Stanford CS 224N "Default Final Project: Build GPT-2" starter codebase:

    CS 224N Default Final Project: Build GPT-2 (Winter 2025)
    https://web.stanford.edu/class/cs224n/

That starter assignment is reused across course offerings. To avoid publishing a
solution to it, this repository deliberately does NOT include the completed
starter (the GPT-2 model, attention, optimizer, classifier, or task scripts).
It publishes only our own extension modules and shows how they were integrated
via short patch snippets (see docs/integration.md).

Parts of the original course codebase derive from the HuggingFace `transformers`
library (Apache License 2.0). None of that code is redistributed here.

Datasets (SST, CFIMDB, Quora Question Pairs, Shakespeare sonnets) are NOT
redistributed; see README.md for where to obtain them.
